
The aim of this study is to describe the role of the zzso in the care of one specified cancer patient per zzso and to explore the zzso knowledge about that patient's disease and zzso A further aim was to evaluate the effects of an extended information routine, including increased information from the specialist clinic to the zzso Twenty zzso were selected for a zzso interview about a patient zzso either to an extended zzso information routine or to standard zzso The results suggest that zzso are commonly involved in the care of cancer patients, particularly in the diagnosis of the disease but also during the period of treatments and zzso The information from the specialist clinic to the zzso is insufficient in standard zzso The extended information routine increased the zzso knowledge about the disease and treatments and facilitated their possibilities to determine patients' need for zzso However, this did not affect the extent of contacts with the zzso 

